snippet.textDisplay:
When two friends (A + B) in a friend group get into an argument, and then A decides to say to B something like, "You're not useful."

After that, B feels down and tries to change themself to show A they're useful. However, because of the argument, A doesn't take notice and even tells B that they are trying too hard.

Eventually, B goes to the rest of the friend group for comfort and says this and all that friend group just instantly sides with them without hearing A's part of the story. B tells them that they need to take a break from A but also tells the friend group that they shouldn't attack A.

Instead of asking A their side of the story, they all just abandon them, without knowing the full story and only going with one half. This is because they can't believe that A could say such things and treating B as unequal. You know, some would even go as far as telling A they deserve to die or that they should kill themself. That friend group? Simple, a lot of the fanbase.

However, there is one person (C) who is there to comfort A through hard times. They listen to both A and B's stories and doesn't try to pick a side. However, after this, the friend group is pressuring them to pick a side.

C, not knowing what to do, leaves the whole friend group entirely and think about what's happening and how this all came to be. Most of the friend group forgets about C and continues with this whole drama.
